SUMMARY:Ignite Reception
DESCRIPTION:Our signature welcome event\, Ignite\, showcases a series of rapid-fire talks from creative thinkers in the museum field. Expect lots of energy with fresh\, inspiring\, and timely ideas from familiar faces and emerging voices in the field and beyond. Talks follow the “Ignite” format\, in which presenters have five minutes and 20 slides (which advance automatically every 15 seconds) to enlighten\, entertain\, and inspire. Hear from several brave and visionary speakers sharing their experiences in a wide variety of disciplines.\n\nDISCARD AFTER _________\nErin Richardson\, Founder and Principal Consultant\, Frank and Glory\n\nThe Museum That Never Was\nIsabella Bruno\, Navigator\, Lab for Radical Museum Futures\n\nLet’s Gleefresh!\nMandy Smith\, Director of Sales and Business Development\, North America\, MuseumINSIDER\n\nThe Unofficial “Data Tour” of the National Gallery of Art\nJulia Demarest\, Data Scientist\, National Gallery of Art\n\nLet’s stand up for museums\nMatt Morgan\, President\, Concrete Computing\n\nLeft Behind by the Hype: What Small Museums Really Need in the Age of AI\nCourtney OCallaghan\, Director of Operations\, Museable\n\nThe Joy of Mapmaking\nRenee Keul\, University of Southern Maine\n\nThe Emotional ROI of a Gallery Bench\nRob Hassler\, Director of Strategic Partnerships\, Bluecadet\n\nThe Myth of ‘Build It and They Will Come’ : What EDM Can Teach Museums About Digital Engagement\nKimberly Lý\, Interactive Media Producer\, Crystal Bridges Museum of American Art\n\nThis reception is included in the registration cost\; no separate ticket is required. Light appetizers and beverages will be provided.
CATEGORIES:EVENT
LOCATION:Dakota\, 1010 Nicollet Mall\, Minneapolis\, MN 55403
